As we celebrate the freedom of Black people during pride month, today made me reflect on how fortunate we are to have come this far. #Juneteenth #pride

When I started in the TV news industry, I had no idea of the life ahead, the things I’d see, the people I’d meet and the places I’d go. After graduating from Temple University, I dreamed of working in a top 10 market and becoming a network correspondent one day. My last two stops, The Black News Channel and ABC13 Houston, helped me accomplish those dreams, and what a journey it’s been. From the US-Mexico border, talking to people doing the unimaginable to get into this country, to Minneapolis, listening to people fight against police brutality, I’ve had one mission the entire time… to give people a voice in a way that makes them feel valued. There have been tough days, covering the pandemic, homicides and people losing everything after a tornado or hurricane destroyed their home. But, there have also been lighter days, covering celebrations, parades, and festivals. It all comes with the job. 

This year, I made a bold decision to step away from TV news. Thinking about what I wanted to accomplish when I first got into this business and fulfilling those dreams played a big part in this decision. I haven’t been on TV since February, and to those who’ve noticed, I apologize for keeping you in the dark! I’ve used the past few months to slow down, reflect on life and dream again. Stay tuned ☺️
Flying planes started out as a video game for me a couple years ago. Now, I fly them for real 😁. I’m back in school! ✈️📚 Flight school to become a pilot 👨🏽‍✈️

During a recent #FedEx tour, I learned the differences between transporting passengers vs. cargo. 
 
💡 Did you know…

1. Most FedEx pilots fly during the night and several accommodations have been made for them to help prevent pilot fatigue. 

2. Memphis is FedEx’s largest hub, and can be the busiest airport in the world during overnight hours. 

3. Cargo can include anything from medicine to hazardous materials and even wildlife.
I’m now a Certified Private Pilot! 👨🏽‍✈️✈️

Passed the FAA’s Instrument written exam today! Whew that was a lot of studying 📚 😭. If you have any questions about aviation, reach out!
